DocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gyk1665702807017.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gyk1665702807017.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gyk1665702807017.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gyk1665702807017\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Literal Name\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Case-sensitive name for the operation for non-Uniface implementations. The literal name should be a maximum of 64 characters. All NLS characters are valid, but the first character must be a letter.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gyk1665702807017__section_shx_54p_dxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d775136e51\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyk1665702807017__p_d111176e1_d111177e1_d111178e1\">Uniface maps the operation name to the literal\n        name.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyk1665702807017__p_d111179e1_d111180e1_d111181e1\">For C implementations only, Uniface generates the\n        default name <var class=\"keyword varname\">ComponentName_OperationName</var> to ensure that it is unique.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gyk1665702807017__section_qr2_w4p_dxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d775136e66\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"gyk1665702807017__ul_flq_x4p_dxb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gyk1665702807017__li_d42788e1_d42789e1_d42790e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dlk1665702714091.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dlk1665702714091.html\" title=\"A Signature Operation is a Development Object that describes the public method of a signature.\">Signature Operation</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613410\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613410\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Literal Name Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Literal Name Case-sensitive name for the operation for non-Uniface implementations. The literal name should be a maximum of 64 characters. All NLS characters are valid, but the first character must be a letter. Description Uniface maps the operation name to the literal name. For C implementations only, Uniface generates the default name ComponentName_OperationName to ensure that it is unique. Applies To Signature Operation Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}